    "content": "## Theorem: translated_imo_2010_p4\n\nTheorem: translated_imo_2010_p4\nGiven: s c p = iso_triangle s c p\nGiven: o = on_tline o c s c\nGiven: a = on_circle a o c\nGiven: b = on_circle b o c, on_line b s a\nGiven: m = on_line m c p, on_circle m o c\nGiven: l = on_line l b p, on_circle l o c\nGiven: k = on_line k a p, on_circle k o c\nProve: prove that segment mk = segment ml\n\nGoal: cong m k m l\n\n## English proof (from stage 1)\n{\n  \"key_observation\": \"After putting the circumcircle in unit-circle coordinates, the condition SC = SP gives an explicit formula for P, and the desired equality becomes a single algebraic identity in the circle parameters of K, L, and M.\",\n  \"plan\": [\n    \"Normalize the circle and introduce a rational parameter for points on it.\",\n    \"Derive the equation of a chord in terms of the parameters of its endpoints.\",\n    \"Use SC = SP and the line CP to express the coordinates of P in terms of the parameter of M.\",\n    \"Use collinearity with P to relate the parameters of A, B, K, L, M.\",\n    \"Prove the algebraic identity equivalent to MK = ML.\",\n    \"Conclude equality of the two chord lengths from the distance formula on the unit circle.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"We may assume the circumcircle has center O = (0,0), radius 1, C = (1,0), and the tangent at C is the vertical line x = 1; hence S = (1,t) for some real t with t != 0.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"A similarity transformation preserves tangency, collinearity, ratios of lengths, and equality of lengths. Since SC is tangent to the circle at C, we may choose coordinates so that the circle is the unit circle and the tangent at C is x = 1.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"similarity transformations preserve incidence and length equality\",\n        \"radius is perpendicular to tangent at point of tangency\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"For a real parameter u, write T(u) = ((1 - u^2)/(1 + u^2), 2u/(1 + u^2))